THE root cause of the CBE compiler's latent heap corruption: two independent
sbrk cursors, both rooted at `end` — Zig std's plan9.sbrk and cc9 n9libc's
n9_sbrk — handing out overlapping memory in one process. Under the C backend
plan9.sbrk now delegates to n9libc's exported, locked cc9_sbrk (one break
owner); native-backend target programs keep the local cursor. Also the
std.os.plan9 gaps the build runner needs: CLOCK, symlinkat (EOPNOTSUPP),
futimens (no-op success; the Cache content-hashes when mtime is unreliable).

